# Why GitHub Matters

GitHub is a platform used for version control and collaboration.

It helps teams manage source code changes and track project history.

### Benefits of GitHub

### Version Control

Tracks all changes made to project files.

### Collaboration

Multiple developers can work on the same project simultaneously.

### Backup and Recovery

Code is stored securely in remote repositories.

### Code Reviews

Team members can review and approve changes before deployment.

### Integration with CI/CD

GitHub works seamlessly with automation tools for testing and deployment.

### Common Git Commands

```bash id="slyuk4"
git add .
git commit -m "Added new feature"
git push origin main
```

### Why Enterprises Use GitHub

* Better collaboration
* Change tracking
* Improved code quality
* Faster development cycles
* Safer deployments

