# Enterprise Workflow Discussion

Modern Salesforce projects follow structured workflows to ensure quality and reliability.

## Enterprise Development Workflow

```text id="m32rrh"
Business Requirements
          ↓
Development
          ↓
Scratch Org
          ↓
Git Repository
          ↓
Code Review
          ↓
Automated Testing
          ↓
CI/CD Pipeline
          ↓
Staging Environment
          ↓
Production Deployment
          ↓
Monitoring & Maintenance
```

---

## Workflow Explanation

### Step 1: Requirement Analysis

Business requirements are collected and documented.

### Step 2: Development

Developers create Apex classes, Lightning Web Components, Flows, and configurations.

### Step 3: Scratch Org Usage

Temporary environments are created for development and testing.

### Step 4: Source Control

Code is committed to GitHub repositories.

### Step 5: Code Review

Team members review code quality and functionality.

### Step 6: Automated Testing

Apex tests and validation checks are executed automatically.

### Step 7: CI/CD Pipeline

Changes are automatically built, tested, and deployed.

### Step 8: Staging Validation

The application is verified in a staging environment.

### Step 9: Production Release

Approved changes are deployed to production.

### Step 10: Monitoring

The system is monitored for issues and performance.

